description: This file defines an interface for a simplistic hash map implementation in C, providing functions for creating, cloning, inserting, retrieving, deleting, and iterating over key-value pairs. It also includes definitions for managing hash map lifecycle and iteration.

classes.name: icHashMap
classes.description: The main hash map data structure.

classes.name: icHashMapIterator
classes.description: Iterator for traversing hash map entries.

methods.name: hashMapClone
methods.description: Creates a shallow clone of an existing hash map.

methods.name: hashMapDeepClone
methods.description: Creates a deep clone of an existing hash map using a provided clone function.

methods.name: hashMapDestroy
methods.description: Destroys a hash map and releases associated memory.

methods.name: hashMapIsClone
methods.description: Checks if a map was created via clone.

methods.name: hashMapPut
methods.description: Assigns a key/value pair to the hash map.

methods.name: hashMapPutCopy
methods.description: Inserts a key/value pair into the hash map, copying the key and value.

methods.name: hashMapGet
methods.description: Retrieves the value associated with a given key.

methods.name: hashMapContains
methods.description: Checks if a key exists in the map.

methods.name: hashMapDelete
methods.description: Removes a key/value pair from the map.

methods.name: hashMapCount
methods.description: Returns the number of entries in the hash map.

methods.name: hashMapClear
methods.description: Clears all entries in the hash map.

methods.name: hashMapIteratorCreate
methods.description: Creates an iterator for the hash map.

methods.name: hashMapIteratorHasNext
methods.description: Checks if there are more items to iterate.

methods.name: hashMapIteratorGetNext
methods.description: Retrieves the next key-value pair in iteration.

methods.name: hashMapIteratorDeleteCurrent
methods.description: Deletes the current item during iteration.
